WEBVTT

00:02.330 --> 00:03.620
Previously
on"Marvel's Inhumans"...

00:03.620 --> 00:05.040
Maximus: The days of
Black Bolt's rigid meritocracy

00:05.040 --> 00:06.040
are coming
to an end.

00:06.040 --> 00:06.920
Bronaja,
You can see the future.

00:06.920 --> 00:08.500
I can build it.

00:08.500 --> 00:09.580
Maximus is trying
to take over Attilan.

00:09.580 --> 00:12.250
Lockjaw, take Karnak
to where Gorgon is.

00:12.250 --> 00:13.290
No, not me!

00:13.290 --> 00:15.250
-Triton is dead.
-This is a rescue.

00:15.250 --> 00:17.000
Triton!

00:17.000 --> 00:18.380
Come right here,
and when they do,

00:18.380 --> 00:19.620
there's gonna be
some serious trouble.

00:19.620 --> 00:21.080
Who doesn't like
a little trouble?

00:21.080 --> 00:22.500
Your reign.
It's done.

00:22.500 --> 00:24.880
Karnak and Gorgon
are gone.

00:24.880 --> 00:26.710
Medusa is writhing
on the floor.

00:26.710 --> 00:28.290
Are you going to
use your voice?

00:28.290 --> 00:29.500
Kill your only brother?

00:29.500 --> 00:31.170
Stop him!

00:32.670 --> 00:33.790
Freeze!

00:33.790 --> 00:35.830
[ Grunts ]

00:35.830 --> 00:37.120
Where did you
send them?

00:37.120 --> 00:38.790
You really think
I'm going to tell you?

00:38.790 --> 00:40.790
No!
-Take her to her apartment.

00:40.790 --> 00:42.330
Lockjaw, wake up.

00:42.330 --> 00:43.210
Medusa: Black Bolt?
I'm here on Earth.

00:43.210 --> 00:44.210
But I will find you.

00:44.210 --> 00:45.210
We are not defeated.

00:45.210 --> 00:46.880
Take care
of the Royal Family.

00:46.880 --> 00:47.920
-"Take care of"?
-Kill.

00:57.920 --> 01:03.210
♪♪

01:03.210 --> 01:08.330
♪♪

01:08.330 --> 01:13.620
Dr. Declan, you're gonna
want to see this.

01:13.620 --> 01:14.750
[ Tablet beeps ]

01:14.750 --> 01:16.040
He might be Inhuman,

01:16.040 --> 01:18.620
and he's being held at
a correctional facility on Oahu.

01:18.620 --> 01:20.420
[ Police car crashes ]

01:22.750 --> 01:23.960
[ Tablet beeps ]

01:23.960 --> 01:25.330
I need to get there.

01:25.330 --> 01:26.880
Tell the driver
to take me to the airport.
Right.

01:26.880 --> 01:28.500
[ Door buzzes ]

01:28.500 --> 01:33.830
♪♪

01:33.830 --> 01:37.040
It's your lawyer.
You got five minutes.

01:37.040 --> 01:39.460
[ Door slams in distance ]

01:39.460 --> 01:44.120
[ Indistinct shouting
in distance ]

01:44.120 --> 01:45.620
What?

01:45.620 --> 01:47.250
Declan: Hello, Sammy.
I'm not your lawyer.

01:47.250 --> 01:48.920
I just said that
to get you on the phone.

01:48.920 --> 01:49.830
My name is Dr. Evan Declan.

01:49.830 --> 01:51.330
What is this?

01:51.330 --> 01:52.960
Listen.
I know your case file,

01:52.960 --> 01:56.920
and I know what actually led
to you being arrested.

01:56.920 --> 02:00.920
You do what I ask,
then...

02:00.920 --> 02:02.540
Then I will help you.

02:02.540 --> 02:03.540
Go on.

02:03.540 --> 02:05.620
I'm on my way
to Hawaii now.

02:05.620 --> 02:06.790
Will you help me?

02:06.790 --> 02:10.290
What do you need me to do?

02:13.290 --> 02:20.960
♪♪

02:20.960 --> 02:24.620
[ Door clanks, indistinct
shouting in distance ]

02:24.620 --> 02:28.330
[ Cell door buzzes, slams ]

02:29.960 --> 02:33.330
Agon: Being King isn't what
you think it is.

02:33.330 --> 02:37.710
Requires sacrifice,
responsibility.

02:37.710 --> 02:39.670
I'm sorry, Dad,

02:39.670 --> 02:43.420
but from what I've seen,
your job is pretty boring.

02:43.420 --> 02:45.500
It's not boring.
He's the King.

02:45.500 --> 02:47.290
[ Chuckles ]

02:47.290 --> 02:51.250
Of Attilan.
All 1,400 people.

02:51.250 --> 02:53.500
Black Bolt,
the day you take the crown,

02:53.500 --> 02:56.880
you will inherit
all of the power

02:56.880 --> 03:00.000
and all the weight of being
the leader of a great people.

03:00.000 --> 03:03.960
Honestly,
I don't want that.

03:03.960 --> 03:06.710
I'd rather just be me.

03:06.710 --> 03:08.790
I wish I could be King.

03:08.790 --> 03:11.750
Sorry it doesn't work
that way, Maximus.

03:11.750 --> 03:13.120
Like,
if I'm killed in battle?

03:13.120 --> 03:15.000
We're not at war
at the moment.

03:15.000 --> 03:16.920
But if he does die,
I'm King, right?

03:16.920 --> 03:21.380
No one is going to die.
I promise.

03:21.380 --> 03:25.500
Both my sons are destined
for great things.

03:25.500 --> 03:32.670
♪♪

03:32.670 --> 03:35.830
[ Door buzzes, clanks ]

03:35.830 --> 03:37.920
Woman:
Guys, coming out! Coming out!

03:37.920 --> 03:39.880
[ Indistinct shouting ]

03:39.880 --> 03:41.210
Captain Pena!

03:41.210 --> 03:42.620
Captain Pena,
how about a statement?

03:42.620 --> 03:43.790
A statement about what?

03:43.790 --> 03:45.920
The individual that sent
two of the city's finest

03:45.920 --> 03:47.120
to the hospital yesterday.

03:47.120 --> 03:48.420
The individual
in question

03:48.420 --> 03:50.080
was involved in a minor
traffic accident --

03:50.080 --> 03:51.460
With a giant cow-dog?

03:51.460 --> 03:53.920
There was no cow-dog.
Cow-dogs don't exist.

03:53.920 --> 03:55.250
I have nothing else to say
on the matter.

03:55.250 --> 03:56.790
Excuse me, Captain Pena --
I just told you,

03:56.790 --> 03:58.380
I have nothing further to say
to the press at this time.

03:58.380 --> 04:01.000
Okay, well,
I'm not the press.

04:01.000 --> 04:02.500
Callisto Aerospace?

04:02.500 --> 04:04.170
You work for the billionaire

04:04.170 --> 04:05.790
who wants to build
a hotel on the Moon?

04:05.790 --> 04:07.790
It's a base, not a hotel.

04:07.790 --> 04:09.670
The hotel would come later.
Uh-huh.

04:09.670 --> 04:11.750
Look, can you just tell me,
did the guy that you arrested,

04:11.750 --> 04:15.040
did he -- did he show any
sort of, like, unusual powers?

04:15.040 --> 04:16.420
I didn't see anything.

04:16.420 --> 04:18.290
Really?

04:18.290 --> 04:20.670
Not even that cop car
flying through the air?

04:20.670 --> 04:22.330
It's funny how
they do that sometimes.
Yeah.

04:22.330 --> 04:24.210
Now,
if you'll excuse me --
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hold on.

04:24.210 --> 04:27.250
Can you a-- Can you just --
Can -- Can you tell me his name?

04:27.250 --> 04:29.040
I honestly don't have
a clue.

04:29.040 --> 04:30.580
Hm.

04:30.580 --> 04:32.500
I'd like to talk to him.

04:32.500 --> 04:34.330
Too bad.

04:34.330 --> 04:36.120
[ Radio chatter ]

04:39.420 --> 04:42.000
[ Door clanks ]

04:45.750 --> 04:48.960
This is the guy?

04:48.960 --> 04:50.670
This is him.

04:50.670 --> 04:53.380
You want me to put him
in solitary?

04:53.380 --> 04:56.040
Put him in gen pop,
but stick it to him.

04:56.040 --> 04:59.250
If he gets rattled
hard enough by our other guests,

04:59.250 --> 05:01.120
maybe he'll be more inclined
to talk.

05:07.540 --> 05:10.920
[ Door opens ]

05:10.920 --> 05:13.040
You and me?

05:13.040 --> 05:14.790
We're gonna have
some fun.

05:14.790 --> 05:16.330
[ Door clanks ]

05:16.330 --> 05:18.960
[ Kid Cudi's "Surfin'" plays ]

05:18.960 --> 05:21.170
Right?

05:21.170 --> 05:23.250
[ Trolly bell dinging ]

05:23.250 --> 05:25.330
♪ Now, I ain't ridin' no waves ♪

05:25.330 --> 05:27.460
♪ Too busy makin'
my own waves, baby ♪

05:27.460 --> 05:29.250
♪ I ain't ridin' no waves ♪

05:29.250 --> 05:31.080
♪ Too busy makin'
my own waves, baby ♪
Young man: Dad!

05:31.080 --> 05:32.960
♪ I ain't ridin' no waves ♪
Hold on, kiddo.
Had to get money.

05:32.960 --> 05:35.000
♪ Too busy makin'
my own waves, baby ♪

05:35.000 --> 05:36.460
♪ I ain't ridin' no waves ♪

05:36.460 --> 05:38.330
♪ Too busy makin'
my own waves, baby ♪

05:38.330 --> 05:40.170
♪ Slow up for no one,
the shogun ♪

05:40.170 --> 05:41.670
♪ Got the magic in my palms ♪

05:41.670 --> 05:43.790
♪ Rhythm go dumb
with them hums ♪

05:43.790 --> 05:45.750
I'm Medusa, Queen of Attilan.

05:45.750 --> 05:46.920
I need money.

05:46.920 --> 05:48.120
♪ Now,
I ain't ridin' no waves ♪

05:48.120 --> 05:50.080
♪ Too busy makin'
my own waves, baby ♪

05:50.080 --> 05:51.420
♪ I ain't ridin' no waves ♪

05:51.420 --> 05:53.000
This is the Queen of Attilan
speaking.

05:53.000 --> 05:55.620
I require money.

05:55.620 --> 05:58.080
[ ATM beeps ]

05:58.080 --> 05:59.460
Please?

06:02.120 --> 06:04.580
[ Birds chirping ]

06:04.580 --> 06:08.670
♪♪

06:08.670 --> 06:12.710
♪♪

06:12.710 --> 06:16.790
♪♪

06:16.790 --> 06:19.500
I like
that you're confident,

06:19.500 --> 06:21.250
but you should know
these fighters

06:21.250 --> 06:22.790
won't be like anything
you've ever seen.

06:22.790 --> 06:25.170
Lucky and me?

06:25.170 --> 06:27.750
We did two tours
in Korangal Valley.

06:30.960 --> 06:34.000
[ Exhales sharply ]

06:34.000 --> 06:36.080
So, you used to be soldiers.

06:36.080 --> 06:37.750
Once a soldier,
always a soldier.

06:39.460 --> 06:41.790
Maximus will be sending
his most elite fighters,

06:41.790 --> 06:44.620
and these are fighters
that I myself have trained,

06:44.620 --> 06:47.170
which -- which means
they're good.

06:48.960 --> 06:52.420
To them,
you'll be like tiny ants,

06:52.420 --> 06:55.290
and they're
superior beings like me.

06:55.290 --> 06:57.040
Can you be killed?

06:57.040 --> 06:59.880
Anything living
can be killed.

06:59.880 --> 07:01.830
Well,
unless they're bulletproof,

07:01.830 --> 07:03.210
I say a fight's a fight.

07:05.500 --> 07:07.750
If you or any
of your friends want to leave,

07:07.750 --> 07:11.420
now's your chance.

07:11.420 --> 07:14.920
Otherwise, you do what I say
when I say it.

07:14.920 --> 07:17.710
Now, this is my fight.

07:17.710 --> 07:21.830
For my cousin Triton,
for my people, and for my king.

07:21.830 --> 07:24.420
We had a king once.

07:24.420 --> 07:26.790
And then Mainlanders came
and decided we were a state.

07:26.790 --> 07:29.540
I'll fight for your king
in honor of mine.

07:29.540 --> 07:32.830
What about you?

07:32.830 --> 07:34.620
Are you gonna be able
to kill your own people?

07:34.620 --> 07:36.500
People you've trained?

07:36.500 --> 07:40.000
If they're a part
of this coup,

07:40.000 --> 07:41.540
I'll be more than happy

07:41.540 --> 07:43.380
to rip their heads
from their necks.

07:43.380 --> 07:45.120
Well, we'd better
get ready, no?

07:45.120 --> 07:50.920
♪♪

07:50.920 --> 07:52.380
Okay, gentlemen...

07:52.380 --> 07:54.170
[ Sighs ]

07:54.170 --> 07:58.290
I want everybody to stay safe,
stay strong, stay focused.

07:58.290 --> 08:01.210
[ Relaxing electronic music
playing in headphones ]

08:18.330 --> 08:20.790
[ Door closes ]
[ Music stops ]

08:20.790 --> 08:22.670
What do you want now?

08:22.670 --> 08:26.540
I've come to see
if you've considered my offer.

08:26.540 --> 08:29.040
I told you
I don't trust you.

08:29.040 --> 08:30.920
[ Sighs ]

08:30.920 --> 08:33.420
Black Bolt
has put us all at risk,

08:33.420 --> 08:36.920
and the others are too afraid
of him to say anything.

08:36.920 --> 08:41.330
If you take that first step,
the others will follow.

08:41.330 --> 08:43.420
How do I know
you haven't killed them all?

08:43.420 --> 08:45.420
Because I don't want
to kill them all.

08:45.420 --> 08:48.670
I don't want to kill anyone.

08:48.670 --> 08:51.290
But if that becomes
my only option...

09:02.620 --> 09:04.420
[ Sighs ]

09:10.420 --> 09:13.710
You want me to make a speech
in front of the Genetic Council?

09:13.710 --> 09:15.460
More of a statement.

09:15.460 --> 09:18.000
Now, you can put it
in your own words.

09:18.000 --> 09:20.790
What's important is making it
clear that you support me.

09:20.790 --> 09:23.000
But I don't.

09:23.000 --> 09:26.170
It's the easiest way to ensure
a peaceful transition of power,

09:26.170 --> 09:29.710
and it gives our family
a way back home.

09:29.710 --> 09:31.620
Our family?

09:33.670 --> 09:36.250
They were my family
long before they were yours.

09:38.170 --> 09:41.290
I never wanted things
to happen this way.

09:41.290 --> 09:43.380
But it's not too late.

09:43.380 --> 09:45.960
If they get word that
you've given me your support,

09:45.960 --> 09:47.920
they'll know
it's no use fighting.

09:47.920 --> 09:49.000
They'll come home.

09:49.000 --> 09:52.210
I-I know you're confused.

09:52.210 --> 09:54.380
But reading these words
to our people

09:54.380 --> 09:57.460
could help
keep our family alive...

09:57.460 --> 10:00.830
what's left of it.

10:00.830 --> 10:03.380
That's all I want.

10:07.040 --> 10:10.960
I'll do it.

10:10.960 --> 10:14.250
But if you go back
on your word,

10:14.250 --> 10:16.000
I promise I'll kill you,

10:16.000 --> 10:18.120
if it's the last thing
I do.

10:21.120 --> 10:22.960
You're so much
like your sister.

10:26.040 --> 10:27.540
I miss her, too,
you know.

10:31.920 --> 10:33.000
Thank you, Crystal.

10:33.000 --> 10:35.080
For what?

10:35.080 --> 10:37.960
For realizing
that it's better

10:37.960 --> 10:41.330
that you do this
out of your own free will

10:41.330 --> 10:43.710
instead of me making you.

10:43.710 --> 10:48.580
♪♪

10:48.580 --> 10:52.210
[ Door opens ]

10:52.210 --> 10:54.420
Any progress
on Black Bolt's whereabouts?

10:54.420 --> 10:55.790
[ Comlink beeps ]
Not yet.

10:55.790 --> 10:56.960
What's taking so long?

10:56.960 --> 10:58.210
This is Earth.

10:58.210 --> 10:59.210
It's a lot bigger
than the Moon.

10:59.210 --> 11:01.330
Fine.

11:01.330 --> 11:03.540
In the meantime,
I know where Gorgon is.

11:03.540 --> 11:07.210
He was stupid enough
to threaten me.

11:07.210 --> 11:09.960
The poor idiot
can never control himself.

11:09.960 --> 11:11.710
He's left his comlink on.

11:11.710 --> 11:13.210
Which means
he'll be expecting us.

11:13.210 --> 11:14.420
Yes, he will.

11:14.420 --> 11:17.330
Nevertheless,
he's a bird in hand.

11:17.330 --> 11:19.460
Take him down,
and you'll be more prepared

11:19.460 --> 11:21.380
for Black Bolt
when you find him.

11:21.380 --> 11:23.210
Gorgon will be tough
to take on alone.

11:23.210 --> 11:25.120
You won't be alone.

11:25.120 --> 11:29.790
I'm sending you down
some backup.

11:29.790 --> 11:31.380
And Mordis.

11:31.380 --> 11:33.920
Don't send Mordis.
He's not a fighter.

11:33.920 --> 11:38.040
He's just...death.

11:38.040 --> 11:39.620
We'll be better off
without him.

11:39.620 --> 11:42.540
Next to Black Bolt, he's the
most powerful weapon in Attilan.

11:42.540 --> 11:44.580
I have no control
over him.

11:44.580 --> 11:47.960
You need to trust yourself,
Auran.

11:47.960 --> 11:50.250
Trust that you can handle
anything and anyone.

11:50.250 --> 11:51.460
I do.

11:51.460 --> 11:54.000
I believe in you,
and I'm sending you Mordis.

11:54.000 --> 11:56.420
Understood, my King.

11:58.000 --> 11:59.670
Eldrac will send them soon.

11:59.670 --> 12:02.500
[ Comlink beeps ]

12:02.500 --> 12:05.750
Your Highness.

12:05.750 --> 12:07.670
You require
my assistance?

12:10.080 --> 12:13.170
How bad an idea is it
for me to open this door?

12:13.170 --> 12:16.040
I suppose that depends
what's on the other side of it.

12:19.040 --> 12:24.250
♪♪

12:24.250 --> 12:27.000
Mordis.

12:29.880 --> 12:31.920
I'm sorry.
I don't see anything.

12:31.920 --> 12:34.330
Does that mean
there's no danger here?

12:34.330 --> 12:36.120
I don't know.
Maybe.

12:36.120 --> 12:37.830
I don't really know
how this gift of mine works.

12:37.830 --> 12:39.880
I have no control over it...

12:39.880 --> 12:42.040
yet.

12:46.290 --> 12:48.500
Unlock the door.

12:48.500 --> 12:57.920
♪♪

12:57.920 --> 13:02.460
Well...hello.

13:02.460 --> 13:06.170
I promised
you'd soon be free.

13:06.170 --> 13:08.790
I'm glad your trusted
in that promise, my friend.

13:08.790 --> 13:11.380
And where is Black Bolt?

13:11.380 --> 13:13.790
I know he didn't
willingly surrender to you.

13:15.330 --> 13:19.120
Follow me.
I'll explain.

13:27.210 --> 13:29.170
[ Comlink beeps ]

13:29.170 --> 13:32.580
Auran, this is Locus.
Eldrac's sending us through now.

13:32.580 --> 13:35.330
Auran: Copy.

13:35.330 --> 13:39.620
♪♪

13:39.620 --> 13:43.620
♪♪

13:43.620 --> 13:47.080
[ Whooshing ]

13:54.710 --> 13:57.620
Hey, Auran.

13:57.620 --> 13:59.210
Mordis.

14:01.880 --> 14:04.290
Just so you know,
I didn't want to be here

14:04.290 --> 14:05.790
any more
than you wanted me here.

14:05.790 --> 14:07.830
What did he promise you?

14:07.830 --> 14:10.830
Freedom.

14:10.830 --> 14:12.830
[ Birds chirping ]

14:12.830 --> 14:17.750
♪♪

14:17.750 --> 14:22.420
♪♪

14:22.420 --> 14:27.000
♪♪

14:27.000 --> 14:30.920
[ Breathing heavily ]

14:41.250 --> 14:45.040
Hello!
Hello!

14:45.040 --> 14:48.380
Whoa.
Hold up.

14:48.380 --> 14:50.000
What do you think
you're doing here?

14:50.000 --> 14:52.000
I-I-I'm looking for my king.

14:52.000 --> 14:55.040
You just made a big mistake.

14:56.620 --> 14:57.920
I don't make mistakes.

15:01.920 --> 15:04.120
You sure about that?

15:07.120 --> 15:11.460
You got a name,
Mr. Quiet Man?

15:11.460 --> 15:16.040
[ P.A. system chatter ]

15:18.040 --> 15:20.000
Just so you know,
one of the good men

15:20.000 --> 15:22.420
you put in the hospital
with that little car stunt

15:22.420 --> 15:24.290
happens to be
my brother-in-law.

15:24.290 --> 15:26.250
And he's gonna spend
the next six weeks

15:26.250 --> 15:27.880
eating all of his meals
through a straw

15:27.880 --> 15:29.750
thanks to you.

15:35.710 --> 15:38.120
Hey, Rivera,

15:38.120 --> 15:39.710
why don't you bring him
by my cell

15:39.710 --> 15:41.330
for a little play time?

15:41.330 --> 15:44.830
See?
You're making friends already.

15:47.580 --> 15:51.380
[ Birds chirping ]

15:53.290 --> 15:55.420
Mordis:
There's trees everywhere.

15:55.420 --> 15:56.830
I mean, can't we go
a different way?

15:56.830 --> 15:58.460
This is taking forever.

15:58.460 --> 16:03.170
Flora: This world is amazing.
I've never seen so many plants.

16:03.170 --> 16:05.290
Hey, Flora.
Huh?

16:05.290 --> 16:06.880
Can't you make a path
or something?

16:06.880 --> 16:09.380
Oh, yeah, sure.

16:09.380 --> 16:10.620
"Oh, sure."

16:10.620 --> 16:13.580
♪♪

16:13.580 --> 16:16.170
[ Rumbling ]

16:16.170 --> 16:24.210
♪♪

16:24.210 --> 16:32.170
♪♪

16:32.170 --> 16:40.170
♪♪

16:40.170 --> 16:48.170
♪♪

16:48.170 --> 16:57.040
♪♪

16:57.040 --> 17:06.040
♪♪

17:06.040 --> 17:14.880
♪♪

17:14.880 --> 17:23.710
♪♪

17:23.710 --> 17:32.580
♪♪

17:32.580 --> 17:41.710
♪♪

17:41.710 --> 17:43.750
[ Waves crashing ]

17:43.750 --> 17:51.330
♪♪

17:51.330 --> 17:58.880
♪♪

17:58.880 --> 18:00.960
[ Sighs ]

18:00.960 --> 18:09.620
♪♪

18:09.620 --> 18:18.000
♪♪

18:18.000 --> 18:26.710
♪♪

18:26.710 --> 18:35.080
♪♪

18:35.080 --> 18:43.710
♪♪

18:43.710 --> 18:52.080
♪♪

18:52.080 --> 19:00.580
♪♪

19:00.580 --> 19:08.540
♪♪

19:08.540 --> 19:16.710
♪♪

19:16.710 --> 19:24.620
♪♪

19:24.620 --> 19:32.290
♪♪

19:37.620 --> 19:39.040
Karnak:
I'm not a threat.

19:39.040 --> 19:40.710
I was lost.

19:40.710 --> 19:43.080
I didn't mean to intrude on
whatever you have going on here.

19:44.710 --> 19:46.420
What the hell
are we doing here?

19:46.420 --> 19:47.960
I mean, I'm pretty sure
tying him up like that

19:47.960 --> 19:49.460
qualifies as kidnapping.

19:49.460 --> 19:51.040
Give me a break.

19:51.040 --> 19:53.670
We're squatting on public land
with more than an acre of ganja.

19:53.670 --> 19:54.920
He could ruin everything.

19:54.920 --> 19:56.540
I say we let him go.

19:56.540 --> 19:58.670
Look at his tats.
There's no way he's a cop.

19:58.670 --> 20:01.500
Then what's this?

20:01.500 --> 20:02.920
'Cause I'm pretty sure
it's not an iPhone.

20:02.920 --> 20:09.120
♪♪

20:09.120 --> 20:10.420
Who you talking to
with this?

20:10.420 --> 20:13.040
No one. That comlink
is clearly non-functional.

20:13.040 --> 20:16.750
Who would you be talking to
if it wasn't busted?

20:16.750 --> 20:19.170
My king.

20:22.120 --> 20:24.290
[ Scoffs ]
King of what?

20:24.290 --> 20:28.000
It doesn't matter.
My family...they need me.

20:28.000 --> 20:31.080
His family?

20:31.080 --> 20:33.830
How do we know he's not with
some cartel come to kill us?

20:33.830 --> 20:37.170
I need to find Black Bolt.
Medusa. Gorgon.

20:38.750 --> 20:40.290
Dude's crazy.

20:40.290 --> 20:42.880
I say we let him go.

20:42.880 --> 20:44.580
Let's say you're right,

20:44.580 --> 20:47.540
and he is just some kook
off his meds.

20:47.540 --> 20:50.790
Then what happens when he blabs
our location to someone?

20:50.790 --> 20:52.580
We've worked too hard
for this.

20:56.290 --> 20:58.210
We've worked too hard
for this.

20:58.210 --> 20:59.710
W-What do you want to do?

20:59.710 --> 21:02.250
Do you want to keep him locked
up until we sell our crop?

21:02.250 --> 21:03.710
No.
We should kill him.

21:03.710 --> 21:09.830
♪♪

21:09.830 --> 21:11.880
What the hell
did you do that for?

21:11.880 --> 21:15.250
Maybe he's a little upset you
just suggested we kill him.

21:15.250 --> 21:18.210
Let's talk outside.

21:23.170 --> 21:25.120
[ Door buzzes ]

21:25.120 --> 21:29.120
[ P.A. system chatter ]

21:29.120 --> 21:31.580
[ Indistinct chatter ]

21:31.580 --> 21:33.080
Man: Hey,
where you going?

21:33.080 --> 21:36.040
[ Laughs ]

21:51.500 --> 21:54.380
♪♪

21:54.380 --> 21:55.670
Where you from?

21:55.670 --> 21:57.420
'Cause I know
you're not local.

22:02.500 --> 22:03.750
How'd you get your abilities?

22:09.920 --> 22:12.210
You gonna talk to me or not?

22:17.960 --> 22:19.460
Oh.

22:19.460 --> 22:21.750
Okay.
I get it.

22:21.750 --> 22:23.880
You can't talk.

22:23.880 --> 22:26.210
Were you experimented on?

22:30.290 --> 22:32.040
Did you get bit
by a radioactive bug?

22:33.670 --> 22:36.040
Or maybe you woke up
one morning

22:36.040 --> 22:40.250
covered in a funky,
rock-like crust.

22:43.500 --> 22:46.210
Yeah.

22:46.210 --> 22:48.750
You know
what I'm talking about.

22:48.750 --> 22:53.380
Look, I'm not your enemy.
I just wanted to warn you.

22:53.380 --> 22:55.960
People like you
are disappearing

22:55.960 --> 22:58.120
from all over.

22:58.120 --> 23:00.790
You got family?
A wife?

23:03.960 --> 23:05.330
Me, too.

23:05.330 --> 23:08.710
If I were you,
I'd get out any way I could,

23:08.710 --> 23:12.210
and find them before something
bad happens to them, too.

23:23.420 --> 23:26.080
'Cause this is Hawaii.

23:26.080 --> 23:28.040
We help our friends.

23:28.040 --> 23:32.790
♪♪

23:32.790 --> 23:34.830
[ Birds chirping ]

23:38.040 --> 23:40.920
[ Device beeping steadily ]

23:44.120 --> 23:47.710
[ Beeping quickens ]

23:54.210 --> 23:57.250
This is it.
He's here somewhere.

23:57.250 --> 23:59.960
Mordis, you stay back
and keep Locus safe.

23:59.960 --> 24:02.250
I don't know if you noticed,

24:02.250 --> 24:05.420
but keep people safe's
not my best quality.

24:05.420 --> 24:07.500
Obey.

24:09.580 --> 24:11.580
[ Sighs ]

24:11.580 --> 24:20.830
♪♪

24:20.830 --> 24:23.170
[ Comlink beeping ]

24:23.170 --> 24:24.880
It's empty.
Be prepared.

24:24.880 --> 24:26.750
This could be a trap.

24:26.750 --> 24:29.040
Traitor.

24:34.120 --> 24:36.500
Auran!
Aah!

24:37.750 --> 24:39.170
[ Electricity crackles ]

24:39.170 --> 24:40.750
[ Grunts ]

24:45.380 --> 24:47.120
[ Hisses ]

24:47.120 --> 24:48.290
Aah!

24:48.290 --> 24:49.960
Holo: Lucky!

24:49.960 --> 24:51.080
[ Grunts ]

24:57.250 --> 25:00.710
[ Rumbling ]

25:25.540 --> 25:27.210
Mordis!

25:27.210 --> 25:30.120
♪♪

25:30.120 --> 25:31.170
[ Gasps ]

25:34.670 --> 25:35.750
Aah!

25:38.250 --> 25:41.250
[ Panting ]

25:41.250 --> 25:43.330
♪♪

25:43.330 --> 25:46.750
Let's go! Go!
Now! Go!

25:46.750 --> 25:50.620
♪♪

25:50.620 --> 25:52.710
[ Grunts ]

25:58.080 --> 26:00.120
[ Birds chirping ]

26:08.290 --> 26:11.290
You and your friends
have come to a decision?

26:11.290 --> 26:13.500
Before your wound
gets infected.

26:13.500 --> 26:15.170
May I?

26:22.710 --> 26:25.040
Part of the plan is to leave
a clean corpse?

26:27.000 --> 26:28.670
Sorry about Reno.

26:28.670 --> 26:30.920
We've sunk all our money
into this thing.

26:30.920 --> 26:32.880
It seemed like a great idea
when we started,

26:32.880 --> 26:35.080
but he's worried
it's all gonna blow up.

26:35.080 --> 26:37.620
I'm not going to get
in your way.

26:37.620 --> 26:38.790
Yeah, well,
when you first arrived,

26:38.790 --> 26:40.620
it seemed like
our little dream

26:40.620 --> 26:42.420
was gonna go poof,
up in smoke,

26:42.420 --> 26:44.380
no pun intended.

26:44.380 --> 26:45.920
You want my advice?

26:45.920 --> 26:47.290
You want to walk out of here,

26:47.290 --> 26:48.920
you got to start
being less guarded

26:48.920 --> 26:50.120
about who you really are.

26:50.120 --> 26:52.880
Start with something easy.

26:52.880 --> 26:54.750
Like your tats.

26:57.380 --> 26:59.620
Um...

26:59.620 --> 27:02.750
it-- it was a decision I made
when I was still a teenager.

27:02.750 --> 27:04.960
The day I got this,

27:04.960 --> 27:07.380
I-I thought it was the greatest
idea I'd ever had.

27:07.380 --> 27:15.210
Now when I look
into a mirror...

27:15.210 --> 27:19.290
it's a -- it's a reminder
of how far I've come,

27:19.290 --> 27:23.000
who I used to be,
and -- and who I am now.

27:23.000 --> 27:25.250
And you are?

27:25.250 --> 27:28.500
I'm someone who doesn't
make mistakes.

27:28.500 --> 27:33.830
Now, since I hit my head,
I-I don't know.

27:33.830 --> 27:37.580
I can't see the consequences
of my decisions

27:37.580 --> 27:42.710
as clearly as I should,
if at -- if at all.

27:42.710 --> 27:44.290
I'm sure it'll be all right.

27:44.290 --> 27:46.750
I'm not so sure.

27:48.790 --> 27:53.580
What I am sure of is that,
in my current state,

27:53.580 --> 27:58.330
I-I'm not of any use
to my family.

27:58.330 --> 28:01.830
I mean, come on.
Your family's family, right?

28:01.830 --> 28:04.420
They'll always
be there for you.

28:04.420 --> 28:08.460
But I-I-I can't be there
for them.

28:08.460 --> 28:13.960
Everyone's always
looked to me for answers.

28:13.960 --> 28:18.420
If it's all the same to you,

28:18.420 --> 28:20.830
I'd like to stay here.

28:20.830 --> 28:27.290
♪♪

28:27.290 --> 28:33.790
♪♪

28:33.790 --> 28:36.500
[ Horns honking ]

28:44.880 --> 28:46.710
Can I help you, Captain?

28:46.710 --> 28:49.460
You're gonna wait out here
all night for nothin'.

28:49.460 --> 28:51.080
You have no clue who you have
in custody, Captain.

28:51.080 --> 28:52.620
And you do?

28:52.620 --> 28:56.000
I at least have the curiosity
to try and find out.

28:56.000 --> 28:57.500
When I get back
from my supper break,

28:57.500 --> 28:58.620
if you're still here,

28:58.620 --> 29:00.170
I'm gonna have
your car towed

29:00.170 --> 29:01.750
with you in it,
if I have to.

29:01.750 --> 29:06.670
♪♪

29:06.670 --> 29:11.420
[ P.A. system chatter ]

29:11.420 --> 29:14.960
[ Door buzzes ]

29:14.960 --> 29:17.170
Get him out of here.

29:18.330 --> 29:20.830
Come on.
[ Grunts ]

29:20.830 --> 29:23.210
You and me,
we're gonna have a talk.

29:25.170 --> 29:27.120
Lookin' forward to it, brah.

29:28.750 --> 29:32.460
[ Door buzzes ]

29:32.460 --> 29:35.250
Let's go out
and get a little exercise.

29:35.250 --> 29:44.210
♪♪

29:44.210 --> 29:46.540
[ Door buzzes ]

29:46.540 --> 29:48.710
Maximus:
Tibor, come forward.

29:54.710 --> 29:56.170
What can I do for you,
Max?

29:59.380 --> 30:00.620
My King?

30:02.620 --> 30:04.500
I need you to draft
a new edict for me.

30:07.000 --> 30:10.120
[ Clears throat ]
A new edict?

30:10.120 --> 30:12.790
I want to abolish
the caste system.

30:12.790 --> 30:17.420
Your Highness, that would
tear our society to pieces.

30:17.420 --> 30:21.670
It's how we determine
every Inhuman's place here.

30:21.670 --> 30:25.540
It's how you place our people
in the mines to suffer.

30:25.540 --> 30:30.250
I want to free them...
for other opportunities.

30:30.250 --> 30:33.540
I have the support
of the Princess.

30:33.540 --> 30:37.290
I'm sure I can count
on your full support, as well.

30:40.170 --> 30:42.420
Please bring in
Princess Crystal.

30:42.420 --> 30:45.170
[ Audience murmuring ]

30:47.920 --> 30:50.000
Do you have any words to say

30:50.000 --> 30:52.170
to our esteemed members
of the Genetic Council?

30:53.580 --> 30:54.920
Where is Lockjaw?

30:57.290 --> 31:01.920
He's...indisposed.

31:01.920 --> 31:04.380
He needs to be here.

31:04.380 --> 31:06.460
How will it look?

31:06.460 --> 31:08.500
Everyone knows
he's always by my side.

31:08.500 --> 31:10.750
He's heavily sedated.

31:10.750 --> 31:13.080
It wouldn't look good.

31:13.080 --> 31:15.420
Besides, do you think
I'm foolish enough

31:15.420 --> 31:18.290
to put you in the same room
as your teleporting hound?

31:18.290 --> 31:19.790
That's not gonna happen.

31:21.250 --> 31:25.830
Just make the speech
like we agreed.

31:25.830 --> 31:28.120
Then you can see your dog.

31:29.830 --> 31:32.170
Fine.

31:32.170 --> 31:33.620
Let's get this over with.

31:33.620 --> 31:39.000
♪♪

31:39.000 --> 31:44.380
♪♪

31:44.380 --> 31:47.250
[ Clears throat ]

31:53.790 --> 31:59.210
Esteemed honorary guests,
Genetic Council,

31:59.210 --> 32:01.000
my brother-in-law Maximus
would like me to say

32:01.000 --> 32:02.960
a few words on his behalf.

32:02.960 --> 32:05.040
Here's what I have to to say.

32:14.080 --> 32:16.040
Maximus is King.

32:19.830 --> 32:21.500
Of no one.

32:25.120 --> 32:26.380
[ Woman gasps ]

32:26.380 --> 32:29.830
Man: It's frozen!
She's getting away!

32:29.830 --> 32:33.250
Kitang: As you know very well,
determining the gifts

32:33.250 --> 32:35.750
bestowed upon us
by the Terrigen crystals

32:35.750 --> 32:39.670
are not always apparent
or easily discovered.

32:39.670 --> 32:43.460
That said,
after comprehensive analysis,

32:43.460 --> 32:46.500
we've determined the nature
of your transformation.

32:46.500 --> 32:49.710
I feel no different.
No difference whatsoever.

32:49.710 --> 32:54.460
Maximus, your transformation
wasn't made manifest

32:54.460 --> 32:57.170
until we looked more closely
at your DNA.

32:57.170 --> 33:02.170
It would seem that you are,
in fact, no longer Inhuman.

33:02.170 --> 33:03.880
What?
What are you talking about?

33:03.880 --> 33:06.380
Of course I'm Inhuman.
I'm afraid not.

33:06.380 --> 33:10.170
You are now, down to the deepest
cellular level of your being,

33:10.170 --> 33:11.620
merely human.

33:11.620 --> 33:13.750
But --

33:13.750 --> 33:17.290
And,
as I'm sure you understand,

33:17.290 --> 33:20.540
no human can ever
be king of the Inhumans.

33:20.540 --> 33:25.210
♪♪

33:25.210 --> 33:28.120
[ Audience murmuring ]

33:28.120 --> 33:31.750
♪♪

33:31.750 --> 33:33.420
You see?

33:35.790 --> 33:38.380
This is how the rest
of my Royal Family

33:38.380 --> 33:40.920
feels about their responsibility
to Attilan.

33:40.920 --> 33:42.580
[ Man shouts indistinctly ]

33:42.580 --> 33:44.000
They run away from it.

33:44.000 --> 33:50.420
♪♪

33:50.420 --> 33:52.170
But I am not like them.

33:52.170 --> 33:53.580
I have never been like them.

33:53.580 --> 33:56.580
♪♪

33:56.580 --> 33:57.960
[ Grunting ]

33:57.960 --> 34:01.170
And my father was right --

34:01.170 --> 34:03.750
I am destined for great things.

34:03.750 --> 34:04.920
[ Pounding on door ]
Lockjaw. Come on.

34:04.920 --> 34:06.880
Wake up.
Time to get out of here.

34:06.880 --> 34:10.920
And I will never turn my back
on the people of Attilan.

34:10.920 --> 34:12.620
[ Applause ]

34:13.710 --> 34:16.420
[ Electricity crackles ]

34:16.420 --> 34:17.500
Take me to where you took
the others.

34:23.710 --> 34:26.540
[ Door opens ]

34:26.540 --> 34:31.290
♪♪

34:31.290 --> 34:33.120
We took a vote
on what to do with you.

34:33.120 --> 34:36.040
I die in service of m--

34:36.040 --> 34:39.830
Get up.
I lost that vote.

34:39.830 --> 34:41.080
You can stay.

34:41.080 --> 34:43.080
As long as you're useful.

34:43.080 --> 34:48.120
I will be keeping my eye on you
and the two of you.

34:50.830 --> 34:55.000
♪♪

34:55.000 --> 34:57.460
[ Indistinct chatter ]

35:06.330 --> 35:08.710
Give me an excuse
to mess you up.

35:08.710 --> 35:18.040
♪♪

35:18.040 --> 35:21.290
[ Chatter continues ]

35:30.170 --> 35:32.040
That's him.
I told you that's him.

35:32.040 --> 35:33.710
That's him.

35:33.710 --> 35:36.920
Yeah, the guy that beat up
all the cops.

35:38.460 --> 35:42.540
[ Chuckles ]
Put it there.

35:42.540 --> 35:43.880
Bring it in.

35:43.880 --> 35:46.670
Yeah!
[ Laughs ]

35:46.670 --> 35:49.960
[ Laughter ]

35:49.960 --> 35:52.540
Let's go.
Back it up.

35:56.380 --> 35:57.790
Man: Whoa.

35:57.790 --> 35:59.040
Pick 'em up.

35:59.040 --> 36:00.880
[ Chatter continues ]

36:00.880 --> 36:03.000
I said pick 'em up.

36:06.000 --> 36:09.170
[ Indistinct shouting ]

36:09.170 --> 36:11.750
[ Alarm blaring ]

36:13.710 --> 36:14.920
Get him! Get him!

36:16.420 --> 36:18.040
Break it up! Get back!
Break it up!

36:18.040 --> 36:20.920
[ Indistinct shouting ]

36:20.920 --> 36:22.790
[ Gas hissing ]

36:22.790 --> 36:25.500
[ Blaring stops ]

36:25.500 --> 36:27.540
Hey!

36:27.540 --> 36:32.920
♪♪

36:32.920 --> 36:38.290
♪♪

36:38.290 --> 36:40.290
[ Blaring resumes ]

36:40.290 --> 36:47.460
♪♪

36:47.460 --> 36:54.540
♪♪

36:54.540 --> 36:56.580
Down here.

36:56.580 --> 36:59.330
We got to get out
into the parking lot.

36:59.330 --> 37:03.250
You want to find your wife,
right?

37:03.250 --> 37:04.670
You stay here,
and the law

37:04.670 --> 37:07.040
will make you disappear
in a federal prison.

37:07.040 --> 37:10.040
That's if they don't
kill you here.

37:11.790 --> 37:13.460
[ Sighs ]

37:13.460 --> 37:15.620
Let me handle this.

37:15.620 --> 37:20.500
♪♪

37:20.500 --> 37:23.120
[ Metal groaning ]

37:23.120 --> 37:24.880
Yeah, I know.
Freak like you.

37:24.880 --> 37:29.170
I woke up one morning
covered in some rock-crust,

37:29.170 --> 37:31.790
next thing I knew,
my hands got like this,

37:31.790 --> 37:33.710
and I accidentally
burned down my house.

37:33.710 --> 37:36.500
Could have killed
my family.

37:36.500 --> 37:40.790
And now I've lost them,
just like you.

37:50.460 --> 37:53.580
According to our testing,
Black Bolt's voice

37:53.580 --> 37:56.420
may very well be
the most powerful

37:56.420 --> 37:59.580
and dangerous gift
in all of Inhuman history.

37:59.580 --> 38:03.790
And I have every reason
to believe that as your mature,

38:03.790 --> 38:07.460
your power
will only grow stronger.

38:07.460 --> 38:09.830
But what does it mean?

38:12.210 --> 38:15.790
It means
that your eldest son

38:15.790 --> 38:18.000
has the power to destroy
all of Attilan,

38:18.000 --> 38:21.080
on purpose or accidentally.

38:25.790 --> 38:30.790
You will never again hear
the voice of your oldest son.

38:30.790 --> 38:38.250
♪♪

38:38.250 --> 38:41.580
Perhaps we should consider
placing the boy somewhere safe.

38:41.580 --> 38:43.000
You mean lock him away?

38:43.000 --> 38:46.960
For the safety of Attilan,
my Queen, and himself.

38:46.960 --> 38:49.290
No.

38:49.290 --> 38:51.580
Absolutely not.

38:53.170 --> 38:55.790
He will learn
to control his gift.

38:55.790 --> 38:58.580
But Your Highness --
He is my son.

38:58.580 --> 39:00.670
Someday, he will be king.

39:00.670 --> 39:06.920
♪♪

39:06.920 --> 39:13.380
♪♪

39:13.380 --> 39:14.710
Go!

39:14.710 --> 39:18.380
[ Alarm blaring ]

39:21.670 --> 39:23.540
What the hell?

39:23.540 --> 39:32.670
♪♪

39:32.670 --> 39:35.250
[ Brakes squeak ]

39:35.250 --> 39:37.580
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

39:39.960 --> 39:43.210
[ Indistinct conversation ]

39:52.080 --> 39:53.790
[ Engine starts ]

39:53.790 --> 39:58.960
♪♪

39:58.960 --> 40:04.080
♪♪

40:04.080 --> 40:06.330
I'm here to help!
Get in!

40:07.750 --> 40:09.420
He's our ride!
Come on!

40:09.420 --> 40:12.920
♪♪

40:12.920 --> 40:16.670
♪♪

40:16.670 --> 40:21.670
Black Bolt!
Hey! Hey! Black Bolt!

40:23.080 --> 40:25.880
No.
Hey! I'm here!

40:25.880 --> 40:29.790
Black Bolt!

40:29.790 --> 40:33.540
♪♪

40:33.540 --> 40:35.120
[ Sniffles ]

40:35.120 --> 40:38.000
What's going on?
Who's in that helicopter?

40:41.080 --> 40:44.040
Who are you?

40:44.040 --> 40:45.670
We are gonna follow
that helicopter.

40:46.790 --> 40:48.420
Now!

40:57.620 --> 41:01.250
♪♪

41:01.250 --> 41:03.420
[ Lockjaw panting ]

41:07.750 --> 41:11.170
[ Groans ]

41:11.170 --> 41:15.000
Come on, boy!
Come on, wake up!

